{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe auto-lander needs an opt-in, machine-readable \"please land this\" intent that agents set and the bot consumes as a lease. Under Fast-Forward-Only `main` (ADR-0040) the label must be **non-gating** (FFO already enforces up-to-date, so gating would be redundant and add a wedge) and **non-sticky** (it is about the current tip). Research (GerriScary/CVE-2025-1568) requires a tight vote ACL.\n\n> **Name collision:** `Autosubmit` must be a **project-authored label**, NOT Gerrit's first-party `autosubmit` submit-plugin (lowercase) â€” the plugin auto-submits on gate satisfaction, which is not what we want. Author our own label.\n\n## What\nAuthor an `Autosubmit` Gerrit label in `infra/gerrit/project.config` and apply it to live `refs/meta/config` (operator cutover â€” detect-only under ADR-0026). Vote ACL restricted to the concrete bot identity: service account **`autolander-bot`**, in group **`Autosubmit Voters`**. ACL line: `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] label-Autosubmit = -1..+1 group Autosubmit Voters`. Register the group's UUID in `setup-project.sh`'s `want=` group dict. `function = NoBlock`; empty `copyCondition`. **This canonical account/group naming is what the epic and downstream stories reference.**\n\n## Scope\nConfig + ACL + cutover ONLY. The service that reads the label is a separate story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `Autosubmit` label added to `infra/gerrit/project.config` with `-1..+1`, `function = NoBlock`, empty `copyCondition` (drops on every new patchset), and explicit value lines: `value = 0 No score`, `value = +1 Land this change` (and `value = -1 Do not land` if the low end is used).\n- [ ] `label-Autosubmit` vote ACL restricted to group `Autosubmit Voters` (containing `autolander-bot`) + Administrators via `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] label-Autosubmit = -1..+1 group Autosubmit Voters`; ordinary users and `addPatchSet` cannot forge it.\n- [ ] `Autosubmit Voters` group's UUID is added to `setup-project.sh`'s `want=` group-UUID dict so the group is provisioned/converged.\n- [ ] Label is NOT referenced by any submit requirement (non-gating; FFO enforces up-to-date structurally).\n- [ ] `config-check` passes; live cutover applied to `refs/meta/config` and verified via `GET /projects/rebar/labels/Autosubmit`.\n- [ ] **Security-invariants artifact:** the ADR-0042 Security invariants section records the \"non-gating label + bot-only vote ACL\" invariant with its concrete checks â€” a `grep` of `infra/gerrit/project.config` proving `function = NoBlock` / no submit-requirement reference, and a `GET /projects/rebar/access` diff vs the pre-cutover snapshot proving only `Autosubmit Voters` can vote the label â€” demonstrating the label cannot weaken the two-vote (`LLM-Review`+`Verified`) gate."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783728921426985001,"uuid":"08d1a7e4-273c-4e97-8663-6ea0046ac8a5"}